    {
        "content": "<p>Also, I wanted to double check that mathlib does not have ordered non-abelian groups.</p>\n<p>As far as I could find there are only things like the following:<br>\n<code>OrderedAddCommGroup</code><br>\n<code>LinearOrderedAddCommGroup</code></p>\n<p>I need linearly ordered groups that are not abelian as a big part of the result of Holder's theorem is that the group is in fact abelian.</p>\n<p>Is there a reason mathlib doesn't already have non-abelian ordered groups?</p>",
        "id": 451037546,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Paul",
        "timestamp": 1720806175
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My recollection is that, when it came up, no one had anything too specific that they wanted to do and hence they were not introduced.</p>",
